Mathematical attribution
------------------------
The definitions and theorems formalized in this repository are due to their
original authors, principally:

  - L. Lovász, "Large Networks and Graph Limits", American Mathematical Society,
    Colloquium Publications 60 (2012) — the comprehensive source followed here
    (cut metric, homomorphism densities, the counting lemma, weak regularity,
    compactness, the separation/inverse-counting theorem).
  - L. Lovász and B. Szegedy, "Limits of dense graph sequences",
    J. Combin. Theory Ser. B 96 (2006) — graphon limits and representability.
  - C. Borgs, J. Chayes, L. Lovász, V. T. Sós, K. Vesztergombi, "Convergent
    sequences of dense graphs" I–II — the convergence/cut-metric theory.

This repository is an **independent formalization** of that mathematics in Lean 4:
the Lean source is original expression. No prose, figures, tables, or other
copyrightable expression from the above works is reproduced here; references to
them (by theorem and section number) are scholarly citation. Mathematical results
themselves are not subject to copyright.

